We now have a stab at a unified build system for unix/linux the idea is that it all
builds nicely from wherever you happen to be in the filesystem.

To make this work, there is now a script directory under the project root containing
	scripts/omega_env.sh	- set up environment for build_omega.sh
	scripts/build_omega.sh	- calls make with correct paths and paremeters

HOW TO USE:
	Invoke omega_env.sh from the project root directory,
	this will add the scripts directory to the path of the logged on user.
	
	Once the paths are setup,from anwhere you can invoke build_omega.sh 
	and it'll call make correctly and build in $OMEGA_WORK_DIR/build.

#///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
#//
#//			IMPORTANT NOTE:
#//
#///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
1) You need to use the environment operator (full stop/period charactor '.') 
	when invoking the enviroment script i.e. ". scripts/omega_env.sh"

2) You need to be in the project root, 
	i.e. where you checked out the code i.e. "~/OmegaV-0.4.2/".

#///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
#//
#//			Example Invocation
#//
#///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
me@freebie ~/projects/OmegaV-0.4.2 $  . scripts/omega_env.sh
	OMEGA_WORK_DIR=/home/me/projects/OmegaV-0.4.2
		type 'build_omega.sh all' to build all modules.
		type 'build_omega.sh all distclean' to remove all autogenerated files
		type 'build_omega.sh oocore' to build the core.
		type 'build_omega.sh ooserver' to build the server.
		type 'build_omega.sh oouser' to build the server user.
	me@freebie ~/projects/OmegaV-0.4.2 $ 

enjoy
